body:
@kevingreer @harupy Thank you for your investigation and for proposing some solutions here. The `MLmodel` file is being parsed in order to render the `Schema` section in the UI (the schema is embedded in `MLModel`) - https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/blob/5add07673760aa4e2659e828c32c49cc5a1596ef/mlflow/server/js/src/model-registry/components/ModelVersionPage.js#L226. However, you're absolutely correct that this error message reflects an undue assumption that all MLflow Registered Model Versions contain an `MLModel` file. 

@kevingreer I'm inclined to agree with your first suggestion to remove this line: https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/blob/5add07673760aa4e2659e828c32c49cc5a1596ef/mlflow/server/js/src/common/utils/ArtifactUtils.js#L40. It should be up to individual components to define behavior for handling absent artifacts. For example, ModelVersionPage already expects `MLModel` to be missing in some cases: https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/blob/5add07673760aa4e2659e828c32c49cc5a1596ef/mlflow/server/js/src/model-registry/components/ModelVersionPage.js#L124-L134

@harupy Do you agree that removing https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/blob/5add07673760aa4e2659e828c32c49cc5a1596ef/mlflow/server/js/src/common/utils/ArtifactUtils.js#L40 is the best course of action?

Can we do `fetch MLmodel if it exists` instead of `always attempt to fetch MLmodel which might not exist`?

pseudo code:

```
const artifacts = list_artifacts_for_this_model_version(...)
if ("MLmodel" in artifacts) {
   const MLmodel = fetchMLmodel(...);
   # do something MLmodel
}
```

> No, I don't. Can we do `fetch MLmodel if it exists` instead of `always attempt to fetch MLmodel which might not exist`?
> 
> pseudo code:
> 
> ```
> const artifacts = list_artifacts_for_this_model_version(...)
> if ("MLmodel" in artifacts) {
>    const MLmodel = fetchMLmodel(...);
>    # do something MLmodel
> }
> ```

Ideally, this would be nice. However, we don't currently have a public API for listing model version artifacts. 

@kevingreer I discussed this offline with @harupy and the other maintainers. We agree that removing https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/blob/5add07673760aa4e2659e828c32c49cc5a1596ef/mlflow/server/js/src/common/utils/ArtifactUtils.js#L40 is the best path forward. Would you be willing to implement this?

