On Databricks, `logErrorAndNotifyUser` contains code for JS exception logging.

cc @sunishsheth2009

@sunishsheth2009 Thanks for the comment! 


> in [ArtifactUtils.js](https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/blob/5add07673760aa4e2659e828c32c49cc5a1596ef/mlflow/server/js/src/common/utils/ArtifactUtils.js#L40) with console.error(error) rather than creating a separate abstraction for it. What do you think?

